A vintage 1950s-style illustration of a stern accountant figure in a brown suit peering through an oversized magnifying glass at rows of tiny, identical worker figurines arranged on a massive ledger book. The scene is rendered in muted sepia tones with pops of IBM blue. The magnifying glass creates a fish-eye distortion effect on the figurines beneath it. In the background, towering filing cabinets stretch toward a hazy horizon. The composition has the slightly anxious, exaggerated perspective of mid-century corporate illustrations, with dramatic shadows and crosshatching textures typical of the era.
